        <section id="Upvan Lake" class="section">
            <h2>Upvan Lake</h2>
            <img src="https://i0.wp.com/bharatbuzzz.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/roamwithsumit_45aa3db315614ab7939d439fb3437386.jpg" alt="Introduction" class="section-image">
            <p>Upvan Lake is a picturesque, man-made lake in Thane, Maharashtra, known for its serene environment and surrounding Yeoor Hills. It's a popular spot for nature lovers and those seeking a peaceful escape. The lake is also a venue for the Sanskruti Arts Festival. </p>
            <p>Tranquil Environment: The lake offers a peaceful atmosphere, making it ideal for walks, picnics, and simply relaxing by the water.Surrounding Hills: The scenic Yeoor Hills provide a beautiful backdrop to the lake. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Tikuji-Ni-Wadi" class="section">
            <h2>Tikuji-Ni-Wadi</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="About Us" class="section-image">
            <p>Tikuji-Ni-Wadi is a popular amusement park and resort located in Thane, near Mumbai, Maharashtra, India. It's known for its water park, amusement rides, and overall family-friendly atmosphere. The park was established in 1981 and spans 20 acres, offering a variety of attractions and facilities for visitors. </p>
            <p>Amusement Park: Features rides like go-karts, roller coasters, a giant wheel, and a dinosaur park. Water Park: Includes wave pools, giant slides, and a kids' pool. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Yeoor Hills" class="section">
            <h2>Yeoor Hills</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Powai lake" class="section-image">
            <p>Yeoor Hills, also known as Yogi Hills, is a scenic spot in Thane, Maharashtra, known for its lush greenery, diverse flora and fauna, and fresh air. It's part of the Sanjay Gandhi National Park and offers opportunities for trekking, bird-watching, and enjoying nature. The hills feature winding roads, steep slopes, and are a popular destination for school trips, family outings, and fitness enthusiasts. </p>
            <p>Location: Yeoor Hills is located in Thane West, near Upvan, and is considered the Thane-side extension of the Sanjay Gandhi National Park. Features: The hills are known for their dense forests, diverse birdlife, and natural beauty. Visitors can explore trails for jogging, trekking, and cycling. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Talao Pali" class="section">
            <h2>Talao Pali</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Talao Pali" class="section-image">
            <p>Talao Pali, also known as Masunda Lake, is a popular lake and recreational spot in Thane, Maharashtra, India. It's known for its boating, water scooter rides, and scenic views, making it a favored destination for locals and tourists. The lake also features a small island with a temple, and is surrounded by walking paths and food stalls. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Ghodbunder Fort" class="section">
            <h2>Ghodbunder Fort</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Testimonials" class="section-image">
            <p>Ghodbunder Fort, located in Thane, Maharashtra, is a historical fort with a rich past. Originally built by the Portuguese, it was later occupied by the Marathas and then the British, who used it as their district headquarters. The fort is known for its unique architecture, including picturesque rooms and massive pillars. It's situated on a hill near the Ulhas river and is a popular tourist attraction. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Vardhman Fantasy Park" class="section">
            <h2>Vardhman Fantasy Park</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Madh Island" class="section-image">
            <p>Address: Shivar Garden, Mira Road East, Mira Bhayandar, Maharashtra 401105.Themed Zones: The park features seven distinct zones, each with a unique theme:Texas Cowboy: A Wild West-themed area with wooden patios and cowboy figures.Greek Village: Features a fountain, statues of Greek gods, and open spaces.Colo Theatrum: An amphitheater inspired by the Roman Colosseum for shows and events.Viva Las Vegas: A thrill and gaming zone with rides like Crazy Frog, Free Fall, and Ferrous Wheel.Wonders of the World: Features miniature replicas of the Seven Wonders of the World, such as the Great Wall of China, Taj Mahal, and Eiffel Tower.Lake Venetia: An artificial lake offering various boat rides, including bumper boats and paddle boats.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="St. John the Baptist Church" class="section">
            <h2>St. John the Baptist Church</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Contact" class="section-image">
            <p>John the Baptist Church is an abandoned and ruined church presently located within the SEEPZ Industrial Area, in Andheri, Mumbai, India. It was built by the Portuguese Jesuits in 1579 and opened to public worship on the feast of John the Baptist that year. It also had an attached graveyard.</p>
            <p>John the Baptist Church generally refers to churches dedicated to John the Baptist, a significant figure in Christianity and Islam. In Christianity, he is revered as the forerunner of Jesus Christ, known for baptizing people in the Jordan River to prepare them for the coming of the Messiah. In Islam, he is known as Prophet Yahya and is also considered a prophet who foretold the coming of Jesus. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Kelva Beach" class="section">
            <h2>Kelva Beach</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="" class="section-image">
            <p>Kelva Beach, located in Palghar, Maharashtra, is a popular weekend getaway near Mumbai. It's known for its 8-kilometer stretch of coastline, lined with Suru trees and golden sand. The beach offers various activities like walking, camel and horse rides, and ATV rides. It's easily accessible by road and rail, with the nearest station being Kelva Road. Key Features and Activities:
            Location: Approximately 80 km north of Mumbai.Accessibility: Easily reachable by train (Kelva Road station) and road.Beach Length: 8 kilometers.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="Butterfly Park – Ovalekar Wadi" class="section">
            <h2>Butterfly Park – Ovalekar Wadi</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Butterfly Park – Ovalekar Wadi" class="section-image">
            <p>Address: Ovalekar Wadi, Owala Village, Takkarda Road, Ghodbunder Rd, Thane, Maharashtra 400607, India.Open: Only on Sundays, from 8 AM to 1 PM.Best time to visit: October to February, as the butterflies migrate to and from the plains during this period, offering better chances of spotting various species. Specifically, October and November are when they migrate to the Ghats, and April and May are when they return to the plains</p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="NaMo Grand Central Park" class="section">
            <h2>NaMo Grand Central Park</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="NaMo Grand Central Park" class="section-image">
            <p>NaMo Grand Central Park is a 20-acre urban park in Thane, Maharashtra, designed to be a green oasis with a focus on sustainability and well-being. It offers various amenities and features like a theme garden, sports arena, lake zone, cycling and jogging trails, and a nature trail. The park is open in the morning (6 AM to 11 AM) and evening (1 PM to 9 PM). </p>
